comment:
* Represents a request for handling an SSL error. Instances of this class are
 * created by the WebView and passed to
 * {@link WebViewClient#onReceivedSslError}. The host application must call
 * either {@link #proceed} or {@link #cancel} to set the WebView's response
 * to the request.

methods.name: public void proceed()
methods.comment:
* Proceed with the SSL certificate. *

* It is not recommended to proceed past SSL errors and this method should * generally not be used; see {@link WebViewClient#onReceivedSslError} for * more information.

methods.name: public void cancel()
methods.comment:
* Cancel this request and all pending requests for the WebView that had
     * the error.
